LAGOS – The downtrend in the local bourse persisted last week as sustained sell offs in market bellwethers weighed on overall performance. Consequently, the All Share Index (ASI) closed in the red on three of the five trading sessions in the week, falling 0.6 per cent week-on-week (W-o-W) to settle at 30,672.79 points. Similarly, year-to-date (YTD) loss expanded to -19.8 per cent while market capitalisation shed N61.8 billion W-o-W to close at N11.2 trillion. Trading activity strengthened as average volume and value traded increased by 5.6 per cent and 31.9 per cent W-o-W to 233.7 million units and N3.0 billion, respectively. The top traded stocks by volume were Zenith Bank with 140.2 million units, FBN Holdings recorded 133.0mp million units) and Diamond Bank with 90. 6 million units while Zenith Bank with N3.3 billion, Nestle Nigeria with N1.9 billion and Guaranty Trust Bank with N1.7 billion topped trades by value. The undulating performance from the prior week was extended into last week as the ASI opened the week bearish before inching 0.34 per cent higher in the next trading session.